    public interface DataHolder
    A data holder object allows the access of additional data on the object that is not simply expressed by its basic type.

    For example, a chest block, which is of the chest type, also has inventory. This inventory is considered extra data, which can be accessed via getData(Class), provided that an implementation exposes that extra data.

    • Method Detail

      • getData

        <T> com.google.common.base.Optional<T> getData(java.lang.Class<T> dataClass)
        Get an instance of the given data class for this block.

        For example, if this block represents a sign, getData(Sign.class) would yield an instance of Sign to change the contents of the sign. However, if this block does not represent a sign, then an instance will not be returned.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of data
        Parameters:
        dataClass - The data class
        Returns:
        An instance of the class
